    <note>Huang(2) Xin [845] Son of Xiaozhuo [3414], whose father moved from Jianning, Pucheng xian to Shuzhou, Taihu xian. Xin was buried in Dongping, Xucheng xian. His great grandfather, Yuanji(2) [18920], served in the administration of the Southern Tang. Cai(1) Juhou's [1650] father-in-law. Zhou Bida, WJ, 33.15b; XCB, 282.2a, 308.14a; Liu Zhi, WJ, 14.3b-6b; Yang Jie, WJ, 14.10a-14a [has order of birth of grandfather Jue [12965] and granduncle, Guan(5) [18921], and identifies ancestors as Jiangxia Huang(2), who moved to Pucheng at beginning of the Five Dynasties]. Still listed as a Pucheng jinshi in Fujian TZ, 147.18b. CBD, 4, 2854-6.</note>
